org.fhaes.preferences.wrappers

Class PrefWrapper<OBJTYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhaes.preferences.wrappers.PrefWrapper<OBJTYPE>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActionWrapper, ChangeWrapper, ItemWrapper, TextComponentWrapper

    public abstract class PrefWrapper<OBJTYPE>
extends java.lang.Object
    PrefWrapper Abstract Class. A wrapper around a preference string Defaults to autocommit (you set a preference value, it is saved automatically). This class is not suitable for generic-ization because compile-time checks are useless; the underlying prefs class doesn't use generics. Thus, OBJTYPE is only used to type-check setValue and getValue (and remove ugly casting)
    Author:
    lucasm
